Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: icolor
Version: 1.1
Summary: ANSI colors interpolated into strings
Home-page: https://github.com/brianmhunt/icolor
Author: Brian Hunt
Author-email: brianmhunt@gmail.com
License: MIT
Description: 

    Here is an example:

        cformat("This is #REDa red string.")

        cprint("This #BLUEstring#RESET has #GREENTwo#{BOLD}Colors")


    ANSI Properties
    ===============
    
      Foreground colors:
    
        BLACK, RED, GREEN, YELLOW, BLUE, MAGENTA, CYAN, WHITE, DEFAULT

      Background colors:

        BLACKBG, REDBG, ..., DEFAULTBG

    
      Attributes:
    
        RESET, BOLD, INVERSE, STRIKE, UNBOLD
        
    
    CHANGES
    =======
    
    
    1.0 (24.06.2012)
    ----------------
    
    - Initial release.
        
        
